  "prompt": "Why are there no healthy fast food restaurants?",
  "response": "There are actually some healthier fast food options emerging, though they're not as widespread as traditional fast food chains. Some examples include:\n\n1. Sweetgreen - focuses on salads and healthy bowls\n2. Chipotle - offers customizable, fresher options\n3. Panera Bread - provides healthier sandwich and salad choices\n4. Chopt - specializes in salads with fresh ingredients\n5. CoreLife Eatery - offers green salads, grain bowls, and lean proteins\n\nReasons traditional fast food restaurants haven't been very healthy include:\n- Lower production costs for processed foods\n- Higher profit margins on less nutritious items\n- Consumer demand for quick, cheap meals\n- Established business models\n- Complex supply chains\n\nHowever, consumer preferences are shifting, and more health-conscious fast food options are gradually appearing in the market. Many traditional chains are also adding healthier menu items to meet changing consumer preferences.\n\nThe challenge remains creating fast, affordable, nutritious food at scale, but the trend is moving towards healthier options.",
